WEBVTT

cue-1
00:00:00.099 --> 00:00:05.719
We use comparative adjectives to compare
two people, places, or things.

cue-2
00:00:06.399 --> 00:00:09.680
They tell us how one thing is different
from another.

cue-3
00:00:10.619 --> 00:00:17.520
For example, in a singular comparison, we
can say, "My dog is faster than your

cue-4
00:00:17.520 --> 00:00:23.339
cat." We can also use them to compare
groups of people, places, or

cue-5
00:00:23.340 --> 00:00:30.299
things. For instance, in a plural
comparison, we can say, "Dogs are faster

cue-6
00:00:30.299 --> 00:00:31.299
than cats."
